text.section:
A nursing referral service agency shall:
Obtain a license from the Department prior to operating as a nursing referral service agency;
Develop and implement a procedure to screen licensed health professionals and care providers that includes the following:
In accordance with subsection (c) of this section:
A State criminal history records check; or
A private agency background check;
Verification of current licensure or certification under the Health Occupations Article;
A basic health screening, including a tuberculosis screening;
Verification of references;
Verification of employment history;
Completion of I-9 forms; and
An in-person interview of a licensed health professional and care provider before any referral of the individual is made to a client;
Institute an internal client complaint investigation process that includes:
Notice to the client or client's representative of the complaint process; and
Protocols to investigate complaints;
Provide notice to clients of the Department's complaint hotline number for complaints about the services provided by an individual referred by the nursing referral service agency; and
Allow clients to accept or reject, at their discretion, any licensed health professional or care provider referred by the nursing referral service agency.
